name: kansas-water-quality-action-targeting-system-kats
notes: This system is a revision of the original KATS system developed in 1990 as a tool to aid resource managers target Kansas valuable and vulnerable water resources for program support. The current KATS system has significantly revised the method of calculating water resource component scores and improved the data quality with geo-referenced resource information. The enhanced KATS system increases the accuracy of assessments conducted by planners in general and especially with respect to smaller HUC-11 watersheds.
